<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-27T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-27T13:00:00-05:00" n="109" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/473: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-27T14:00:00-04:00">August 27,
                                    1935—2 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>230. Your 407, August 27, noon, is eminently satisfactory to us. We
                            approve your not making the suggestions contained in the last sentence
                            of our instructions and authorize you to bring them up in your
                            discretion if and when the occasion calls for this.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>